    "key": "f89432372d7838352fd092044f6d88e4786fc6dcc2e7fec97b3f8b3504fb0d15",
    "original": "If one divorces the horror of the act from its utility, there are few phenomena more marvelous in nature than the Nachzehrer's ability to recover by eating the flesh of the dead. No longer! Now man himself may take on such qualities, and without committing crimes of conscience, to boot!",
    "translation": "",
    "context": "this.m.Description = \"If one divorces the horror of the act from its utility, there are few phenomena more marvelous in nature than the Nachzehrer's ability to recover by eating the flesh of the dead. No longer! Now man himself may take on such qualities, and without committing crimes of conscience, to boot!\""
  },
